3.2.2.5 File Sharing

windows file sharing samba is the clear winner 
samba allow a linux machine to behave like a windows machine so it can share files and participate in a windows  domain 
Samba implements the server components, such as making files available for sharing and certain Windows server roles, and also the client end so that a Linux machine may consume a Windows file share.

DNS useed to conver a domain name into an unique ip address of the machine 


Netatalk project 

The Netatalk project lets a Linux machine perform as an Apple Macintosh file server.
DNS also holds global information like the address of the MTA for a given domain name

Internet Software Consortium maintains the most popular DNS server, simply called bind after the name of the process that runs the service.

The Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is one common directory system which also powers Microsoft’s Active Directory.

OpenLDAP is the dominant program used in Linux infrastructure.

Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP)